I am offering a pristine condition 1945 Izhevsk M44 Mosin Nagant carbine. This comes with the attached folding bayonet. This specimen is in fantastic condition and I would guess it was unissued. The numbers on the butt plate, barrel, magazine, and bolt are all matching. 

The wood stock is in perfect condition, no dents, bumps, scrapes, cracks, or gouges. I DID refinish the wood myself, however. The original lacquer job was in such poor condition, it was flaking off everywhere and getting into the action. title: For Sale:  A lot of scammers out there
postcontent:
Some scammers:
The people selling the FN Five-Seven for 900-1000. The people selling the Desert Eagles for 800-1000. The Kel Tec PMR-30 is a hot one too. You can see what other scams they got going on by clicking "Listings by this User". Flag them all.

1. They only respond to your inquiry when you tell them that you are too far away to pick up the gun. They then respond and say send me your FFL and I will mail the gun to you. They don't have said gun. You wont get it. Only pics stolen from the interweb.

2. They are a dealer but fail to identify themselves in their post or in their response.

3. They sometimes have poor English

title: For Sale:  German K98K Mauser matching
location: West Little Rock, Little Rock, Arkansas
postcontent: 1939 K98K German 8 mm Mauser with code 27 on the receiver. Code 27 was formerly S27, which stood for Erfurter Maschinenfabrik (Erma). The receiver, barrel, rear sight group, bolt group including firing pin, bolt release, floor plate assembly, follower, trigger group screws, bands, bayonet lug, and stock are all matching. The stock has not been sanded and has an original K98K sling, but no serial number or other markings are visible. The bore is excellent with no import mark on the barrel and the stock has not been cut. Still has most of the finish except for the butt plate. Erma stopped production of the K98K in 1941, and the serial number of this rifle is #194, making it a fairly early, hard to find variant. I am a collector but I will ship out of Arkansas. I must have a C&R or FFL for shipment and it must be legal for your state. Price would be plus shipping/insurance. $1495.00. This is not a russian capture, yugo, or any of the other imported, mismatched, crap out there. Please don't waste your time or mine with offers not consistent with current, matching K98K prices.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Custom-built AR Rifle: POF-USA P415 18" .223/5.56 upper (original style) with Leupold Mark 4 CQ/T, Slidefire stock, and lots more
postcontent:
Up for sale (with possible partial trade; see below) is my early-gen POF-USA 18" upper AR mounted on an Aero Precision lower, Slidefire stock, and a bunch of other stuff noted below. This rifle has seen a decent amount of (non-military) use and a number of rail sections/corners have had their black worn down to metal (especially the scope), and there are of course scratches here or there, but it functions wonderfully (never had a misfire or other failure, regardless of ammo and/or other conditions) and is fully broken in. See below for details on the rifle build.

Since Armslist only gives me 3 pics, here's a link to a Flickr album that contains a bunch of different ones covering all aspects of this rifle. (Sorry that my phone's camera sucks, but I don't even know anyone who owns a real camera anymore...)

Album: https://www.flickr.com/photos/90749279@N05/sets/REDACTED3666115/

Here's the primary parts/accessories the rifle comes with:

* POF-USA P415 .223/5.56mm upper with a POF-12SX rail system (older style; circular with horizontal cooling vents, and the rear half is covered in a textured coating that works well with gloves. Although it probably didn't need it, I also polished the bore.)
* Aero Precision Lower with DPMS LPK (personally hand-built; I picked out the best-looking pieces from 3 different parts kits for the internals. Billet aluminum in mil-spec tolerances, trigger is single-stage and standard weight but crisp and works great with the Slidefire stock)
* Slidefire SSAR-15 bump-fire stock (it took me all of 1 mag to gain full control of this, thanks to the slightly extra felt-recoil of the POF piston system. Very controllable and fun as hell to use.)
* Leupold Mark 4 CQ/T 1x-3x illuminated scope with A.R.M.S. throw-lever rail mount and Leupold scope covers (As noted above the scope's rails are pretty worn, but the optic itself holds its zero, functions flawlessly and is currently sighted in to provide the best "averaged" zero for a variety of different loads.)
* Troy Industries Folding Battle Sights (front and back, M4 style)
* MagPul B.A.D. Lever
* Grip Pod (Military style, with the metal leg inserts. Comes complete with some dirt from the Middle East.)
* Mil-spec buffer tube with H2 buffer (I'm pretty sure I used a H2, although I'm not 100% positive) and left-side single point sling attachment

Unless you don't want them for some reason, I'm also throwing in 2 C-Products military-spec 30-round mags for free, plus 135 hand-loaded, mil-spec 75-grain HPBT bullets loaded in Lake City Brass with other quality components (including Bench Rest primers), specifically pressure-tested, head-spaced and blah-blah hand-loading-jargon specifically for this rifle.

Although the $3100 price is pretty firm, I'm looking to put together an AR pistol with the proceeds so I've got a list of items that I'd be willing to for trade value (see below). I'm willing to do FtF, ship to your FFL, payment via various methods, etc. It's a big investment so I'll work with you to make the transaction as easy as possible for you.
